{"title":"Macworld Podcast: Your hot takes on big iMacs, iOS 17 features, Apple GPT, and more","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2006479/hot-takes-big-imacs-ios-17-features-apple-gpt.html","date":1690443000000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>On this episode of the Macworld Podcast, it’s all about your hot takes! You have thoughts on the latest happenings in the world of Apple! Let’s hear what you have to say!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is episode 850 with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Jason-Cross/\" target=\"_blank\">Jason Cross</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Michael-Simon/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Simon</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Roman-Loyola/\" target=\"_blank\">Roman Loyola</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 850 on Apple Podcasts</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 850 on Spotify</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This episode is all about Macworld reader and listener hot takes. You have thoughts and we’re going to share and respond to what you wrote. All of the comments mentioned in the show can are listed below.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>To beta or not to beta </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As most of you all know, Apple releases betas or its operating systems, and Apple has a public beta program that users can join if they want to try out the new software. Jason Snell recently wrote a column <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2000748/why-you-should-install-apple-public-betas.html\">encouraging users to install the betas on their iPhone, iPads, and Macs</a>, reasoning that you can help Apple make better software.  However, not everyone agrees with him.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Have you all fully lost your minds?</p>— Jordan (@tlg_jordan) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/tlg_jordan/status/1682223259524251648?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 21, 2023</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/davenport-macos-beta.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"Davenport Beta Facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/davenport-macos-beta.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1956w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/davenport-macos-beta.jpg?resize=300%2C63&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/davenport-macos-beta.jpg?resize=768%2C163&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/davenport-macos-beta.jpg?resize=1200%2C254&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/davenport-macos-beta.jpg?resize=1536%2C325&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"254\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid028soDeXoxjgk2wTxhL73N6MUs7zeRXbRB7awVjwBUw4P3ro5oWockQbMfXNb86MJcl%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>A bigger iMac </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Bloomberg reported that <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/1966933/imac-larger-than-30-inches-development-launch-specs.html\" target=\"_blank\">Apple is working on an iMac with a screen that’s over 32 inches</a>. Apparently, that’s something a lot of our readers want.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>I desperately wanted a 30” iMac but Apple refused to ship one, so like many I went with a Mac Studio + Studio Display instead. I’m happy with them both, but I really wanted something a bit bigger than a 27” display.</p>— Jason Dunn 🇺🇦 (@jasondunn) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/jasondunn/status/1673388961337847810?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">June 26, 2023</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"boulden imac facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?resize=300%2C58&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?resize=768%2C148&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?resize=1200%2C231&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?resize=1536%2C296&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/boulden-imac.jpg?resize=2048%2C395&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"231\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02vBPjvijVJvgVDgHaConbpZpqeQH8PMxQrfRB7hHndcha8eEoPUxA45mwn69Kn84Tl%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"pennett imac facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?resize=300%2C59&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?resize=768%2C152&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?resize=1200%2C238&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?resize=1536%2C304&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/pennett-imac.jpg?resize=2048%2C406&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"238\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02vBPjvijVJvgVDgHaConbpZpqeQH8PMxQrfRB7hHndcha8eEoPUxA45mwn69Kn84Tl%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"siddique imac facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?resize=300%2C53&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?resize=768%2C135&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?resize=1200%2C210&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?resize=1536%2C269&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/siddique-imac.jpg?resize=2048%2C359&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"210\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02vBPjvijVJvgVDgHaConbpZpqeQH8PMxQrfRB7hHndcha8eEoPUxA45mwn69Kn84Tl%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"duggan imac facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?resize=300%2C53&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?resize=768%2C135&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?resize=1200%2C211&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?resize=1536%2C271&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/duggan-imac.jpg?resize=2048%2C361&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"211\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02vBPjvijVJvgVDgHaConbpZpqeQH8PMxQrfRB7hHndcha8eEoPUxA45mwn69Kn84Tl%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"jenzo imac facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?resize=300%2C62&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?resize=768%2C158&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?resize=1200%2C247&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?resize=1536%2C317&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/jenzon-imac.jpg?resize=2048%2C422&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"247\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02vBPjvijVJvgVDgHaConbpZpqeQH8PMxQrfRB7hHndcha8eEoPUxA45mwn69Kn84Tl%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Apple is never first with features </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>One of the <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/1970317/ios-17-gives-nfc-new-life.html\">new features in the upcoming iOS 17 is NameDrop</a>, which allows iPhone users to quickly exchange contact info using near-field communications. The thing is, this kind of feature has been on Android phones for a while, and a lot of people really wanted to run with this concept on Facebook. </p>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/yong-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"yong namedrop facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/yong-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1970w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/yong-namedrop.jpg?resize=300%2C42&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/yong-namedrop.jpg?resize=768%2C108&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/yong-namedrop.jpg?resize=1200%2C168&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/yong-namedrop.jpg?resize=1536%2C215&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"168\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02CkmeE2ZhBTvP9v2moG1Unum2mtFPeKphTRfTuRYSAtCPJ3DuEeY53oLQaXEqEkBel%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/fabdubve-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"fabdude namedrop facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/fabdubve-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1960w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/fabdubve-namedrop.jpg?resize=300%2C42&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/fabdubve-namedrop.jpg?resize=768%2C108&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/fabdubve-namedrop.jpg?resize=1200%2C169&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/fabdubve-namedrop.jpg?resize=1536%2C216&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"169\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02CkmeE2ZhBTvP9v2moG1Unum2mtFPeKphTRfTuRYSAtCPJ3DuEeY53oLQaXEqEkBel%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"seta namedrop facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?resize=300%2C53&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?resize=768%2C135&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?resize=1200%2C210&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?resize=1536%2C269&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/seta-namedrop.jpg?resize=2048%2C359&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"210\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02CkmeE2ZhBTvP9v2moG1Unum2mtFPeKphTRfTuRYSAtCPJ3DuEeY53oLQaXEqEkBel%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/meyer-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"meyer namedrop facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/meyer-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2024w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/meyer-namedrop.jpg?resize=300%2C42&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/meyer-namedrop.jpg?resize=768%2C107&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/meyer-namedrop.jpg?resize=1200%2C167&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/meyer-namedrop.jpg?resize=1536%2C214&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"167\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02CkmeE2ZhBTvP9v2moG1Unum2mtFPeKphTRfTuRYSAtCPJ3DuEeY53oLQaXEqEkBel%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"honders namedrop facebook\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?resize=300%2C70&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?resize=768%2C179&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?resize=1200%2C279&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?resize=1536%2C358&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/honder-namedrop.jpg?resize=2048%2C477&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" width=\"1200\" height=\"279\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02CkmeE2ZhBTvP9v2moG1Unum2mtFPeKphTRfTuRYSAtCPJ3DuEeY53oLQaXEqEkBel%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n<div><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all&amp;w=1200\" alt=\"sustaita namedrop facebook\" width=\"1200\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?quality=50&amp;strip=all 2100w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?resize=300%2C46&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 300w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?resize=768%2C117&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?resize=1200%2C183&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?resize=1536%2C234&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1536w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/sustaita-namedrop.jpg?resize=2048%2C312&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 2048w\" /></figure><a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://www.facebook.com/Macworld/posts/pfbid02CkmeE2ZhBTvP9v2moG1Unum2mtFPeKphTRfTuRYSAtCPJ3DuEeY53oLQaXEqEkBel%20&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\" target=\"_blank\">Foundry</a></div>\n\n\n\n<h2>Apple GPT </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Our final story for the show is about a recent report by Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman that <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2000557/apple-gpt-chatbot-genreative-ai-siri-2024.html\" target=\"_blank\">Apple has been doing its own work in generative AI</a> for some time now. Most people were introduced to generative AI with ChatGPT, and it’s taken off, but people are wondering what Apple plans to do with it.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>A friend once quipped that it was Steve Jobs' goal to create the perfect computer, place it in a glass case, and not let anybody ever use it.</p>— designr (@designr_bd) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/designr_bd/status/1682093348189011968?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">July 20, 2023</a></blockquote>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Subscribe to the Macworld Podcast</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You can subscribe to the Macworld Podcast—or leave us a review!—<a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/podcast/id563933198&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">right here in the Podcasts app</a>. The Macworld Podcast is also <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://open.spotify.com/show/3uyZkE4tjbwNNrJCLsBUAM?si=OdOljEAYQvC_ewEsMfKzXA&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com/feed\">available on Spotify</a>. Or you can point your favorite podcast-savvy RSS reader at: <code>https://feeds.megaphone.fm/macworld</code></p>\n\n\n\n<p>To find previous episodes, visit <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/opinion/podcast\">Macworld’s podcast page</a> or our home on <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://cms.megaphone.fm/channel/macworld&amp;xcust=1-1-2006479-1-0-0&amp;sref=https://www.macworld.com